Document: AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamgeneratorplayback.rst
Summary: Methods for managing audio buffer operations including checking capacity, clearing, and pushing audio data.

Method: can_push_buffer(amount: int) → bool
Returns true if a buffer of the size amount can be pushed to the audio sample data buffer without overflowing it, false otherwise.

Method: clear_buffer() → void
Clears the audio sample data buffer.

Method: get_frames_available() → int
Returns the number of frames that can be pushed to the audio sample data buffer without overflowing it. If the result is 0, the buffer is full.

Method: get_skips() → int
Returns the number of times the playback skipped due to a buffer underrun in the audio sample data. This value is reset at the start of the playback.

Method: push_buffer(frames: PackedVector2Array) → bool
Pushes several audio data frames to the buffer. Note: push_buffer() is more efficient in C# and GDExtension but less efficient in GDScript compared to push_frame().

Method: push_frame(frame: Vector2) → bool
Pushes a single audio data frame to the buffer. Note: push_frame() is more efficient in GDScript compared to push_buffer() in C# and GDExtension.